This paper discusses a denial-of-service-based attack on Tor, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack involves disrupting the communication flow in the network, which also relates to network security (cs.NI). The paper also proposes algorithms for detecting such attacks, which involves analyzing and processing data, falling under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and software engineering (cs.SE).
